    "Jin et al. (2018) utilized GloVe to capture semantic information from source prompts, filtering out extreme essays to train a prompt-dependent model.",
    "FastText is an extension of Word2Vec that provides embeddings at both the character and word-level (Bojanowski et al. 2016).",
    "This type of embedding can be beneficial for generating embeddings for out-of-vocabulary (OOV) words.",
    "Ridley et al. (2020 Ridley et al. (, 2021)) proposed the utilization of part-of-speech (POS) embeddings to learn syntactic representations of essays and apply them for cross-prompt essay scoring.",
